definitions.definition: The meat of a deer , typically one that had lived in its own natural habitat.
examples: After shooting a deer, field dressing is the next step necessary for high quality venison .

definitions.definition: The meat of any wild animal that has been hunted rather than raised domestically.

main_definition: The meat of a deer , typically one that had lived in its own natural habitat.
secondary_definitions: ( South Africa ) The meat of an antelope .
( obsolete ) The meat of any wild animal that has been hunted rather than raised domestically.
